LS60 | Ethics, Biotechnology, and the Future of Human Nature | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=LS60 Ethics, Biotechnology, and the Future of Human Nature | instructors: Douglas A. Melton and Michael J. Sandel term:Half course (fall term). M., 2–4, and a weekly section to be arranged. description:Note: Expected to be given in 2015–16.    May not be taken concurrently with Government 1093. May not be taken for credit if Government 1093 has already been taken. The course is open to both science and non-science concentrators. Ethical Reasoning 22 (Justice) is recommended as a background. This course, when taken for a letter grade, meets the General Education requirement for Ethical Reasoning. 
